<br>
Wait, lemme rephrase...<br>
<br>
The first half of Stargate the movie is terrific.  The second half of Stargate the movie is utter filth.<br>
<br>
It had a great start.  It was intelligent, engaging, cool looking, etc.<br>
<br>
But man, the second half... my dog could've written a better screenplay (and I don't even own a dog!).<br>
<br>
I suppose the climax of stupidity would be when the little retarded nomad kid gets blown up, and the film goes into slow motion because they think we're supposed to be heartbroken.  I assure you, I was cheering.<br>
<br>
In fact, that seems to be the defining way to tell if an action movie is good or bad.  When someone gets their ass kicked in slow motion... do you care?  LoTR - Yes, D&amp;D Movie - No, Platoon - Yes, Stargate - No, Etc.<br>
<br>
- Syll<br>
